race.comment: MERCURY EIGHT (3) looks well placed back to Balaklava and back to this class. He is a multiple winner at this track and distance. Opperman looks a suitable booking and expect he will be hard to beat. LAKEHURST (11) is the map horse from barrier three. He is another that will be hard to beat on his best form. MAGIC FIELD (1) has been doing all his recent racing on heavy tracks, which he's unlikely to see here. The 62kg is some concern as well so perhaps best to play each-way. RICH LADY (9) often runs well but rarely wins. She is a place chance, as is NOSIE BY NATURE (5) who is better than what his recent form suggests. This is the easiest race he's tackled in some time and expect he can improve sharply.
